CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 23, 1954, pg. 23, reads: "Cop Second Crown - The women's bowling team of the Centre Avenue Branch Young Men's Christian Association won their second straight National YMCA Championship. Team members, left to right: Louise Coleman, Myre Hannon, Mildred Price, Louise Fulton, Juanita Page, captain and Ethel Bruce.  James M. Burgette, branch executive, is receiving the trophy from team captain Page. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six women of bowling team, from left: Louise Coleman, Myra Hannon or Davis, Mildred "Millie" Price wearing necklace, Louise Fulton, Juanita Page, Ethel Bruce, and James M. Burgette holding bowling trophy from national YMCA championship, in bowling alley
